OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FShabana Mahmood is one of the
OL,7,Foutstanding politicians of this
OL,8,Fgeneration. She is admired across the
OL,9,Fpolitical spectrum.
OL,11,FThis morning, the home secretary is
OL,12,Fcited everywhere, including the splash
OL,13,Fin the Financial Times, as Andy
OL,14,FBurnham's chancellor.
OL,16,FReaction in the gilt or government
OL,17,Fbond market this morning? Zilch.
OL,19,FReaction among Labour MPs across all
OL,20,Fwings of the party, left, right and
OL,21,Fcentre? Eek.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FBecause successful governments of the
OL,7,Fpast 40-plus year have all had at the
OL,8,Fcentre powerful chancellors with a
OL,9,Fvision of how the economy works, from
OL,10,FHowe, to Lawson, to Brown to Osborne.
OL,12,FVisions all different. Ability to
OL,13,Fdrive important change all shared.
OL,15,FAnd although Mahmood may have such a
OL,16,Fvision and a plan, she has shown no
OL,17,Fevidence of it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FShe did a brief stint more than ten
OL,7,Fyears ago, shadowing junior Treasury
OL,8,Fministers, but she has never evinced
OL,9,Fany great interest in or manifested
OL,10,Fany solutions for the great challenge
OL,11,Ffaced by Burnham: how to end almost 20
OL,12,Fyears of stagnation in productivity,
OL,13,Fgrowth and living standards?
OL,15,FSo what on earth is going on? Why
OL,16,Fwould Burnham choose her?
OL,18,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,19,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,20,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,21,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FHere is the shorthand.
OL,8,FHis ally-who-would-be-chancellor, Ed
OL,9,FMiliband, is seen as too disliked by
OL,10,Ftoo many powerful interests, from
OL,11,Ftrade union leaders to business
OL,12,Fleaders, to investors and the right-
OL,13,Fwing media.
OL,15,FThat he almost certainly has the best
OL,16,Fqualifications to be chancellor - deep
OL,17,Fknowledge of how the Treasury works
OL,18,Fand an economic vision - is seen as
OL,19,Fnot enough.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FBut why rule out other candidates,
OL,7,Fsuch as Yvette Cooper, who does have
OL,8,Fdeep experience of the Treasury, or
OL,9,FWes Streeting, who has articulated a
OL,10,Fprogramme that actually looks like a
OL,11,Fgrowth plan?
OL,13,FOr why not skip a generation, as
OL,14,FCameron did with Osborne, and appoint
OL,15,Fsomeone who knows a thing or two about
OL,16,Feconomics and has been an important
OL,17,FBurnhamite, such as Miatta Fahnbulleh.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FWell, according to those who know
OL,7,FBurnham's mind, he and his transition
OL,8,Fteam just want someone at Number 11
OL,9,Fwho will simply execute their will.
OL,10,FThe plan is to drive the economy from
OL,11,F10 Downing Street.
OL,13,FOn this model, poor Mahmood would be a
OL,14,Fcipher for Burnham and his cabal. And
OL,15,Fshe would be a fabulous cipher at
OL,16,Fthat, because her revealed skill at
OL,17,Fthe Home Office is to brook no
OL,18,Fopposition from officials and to drive
OL,19,Freform.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FIf this is Burnham's plan, it is
OL,7,Fhugely risky, and I suspect it would
OL,8,Fend in tears.
OL,10,FBurnham won't personally have the time
OL,11,Fto micromanage the Treasury. No prime
OL,12,Fminister does.
OL,14,FAnd the Treasury, like no other
OL,15,Fdepartment, can only be led by someone
OL,16,F- the chancellor - with personal
OL,17,Fexpert authority and a plan. In all
OL,18,Fother circumstances, the chancellor is
OL,19,Fled by officials.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1784234868
OL,3,CPeston: Is Mahmood the right pick for
OL,4,Cchancellor?
OL,6,FAlso I very much doubt Mahmood would
OL,7,Fallow herself to be any prime
OL,8,Fminister's puppet or cipher in any
OL,9,Fcase.
OL,11,FBy far the biggest decision Burnham
OL,12,Fwill take in his first days as prime
OL,13,Fminister is his choice of chancellor.
OL,15,FIt is possible he has an insight into
OL,16,FMahmood's economic expertise that is
OL,17,Fyet to be seen and heard by the rest
OL,18,Fof the world - or even by his most
OL,19,Fintimate allies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
